Early Access Review

This game is suitable for players looking for an FPS different from those on the market at the moment.

Pros:

+Great atmosphere: sounds, environment,deadly anomalies make this game distinct from the rest;

+Camo matters: non-shiny equipment in green/camo pattern helps you stay disguised to ambush non-suspecting foe;

+Sounds matter: slowing down to listen to your surroundings gives you an edge in close quarters;

+Maps with changing weather conditions: sunny day/rainy day/clear evening etc. make every match feel different;

+Equipment Trade-off system: heavier armour to survive a head-on firefight or resistance to environmental hazard to move through anomalies and perform flanking maneuvers - you chose!;

+Equipment level match-making: you will be matched according to the highest ranked piece of equipment you carry into battle, which, imho, makes the game more balanced and makes you think twice about your load-out;

+4 unique factions: every faction offers a unique line of firearms, equipment and armour which you can combine by freely switching between factions! To gain access to a certain level of equipment you have to gain reputation of your faction of choice by completing combat related missions;

+Equipment upgrades: you can turn every generic piece of equipment into a custom one by upgrading it;

+Artifacts: You can fit your equipmet to be able to collect and use artifacts,which can in turn boost your armour, regeneration speed, movent speed etc;

+Game looks great even on low graphics settings;




Cons ( mostly related to the Early access"  state of the game:

-Bugs and server instability: ping fluctuations and FPS drops
note: if your game crashes you can reenter into the same match (imho a Pro of this game)

-North American servers will have few players and joing the European or Russian ones would mean higher ping and vice versa;

-Some cheathers which get banned quite quickly with the bab lists being regularly published;

-Updates don't always bring optimization improvements into the game;

I do recoomend this game and can give it a 7/10.

